  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-t">FAQ</div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">When does the midnight sun occur in Tromsø?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">The sun does not set in Tromsø from approximately 20 May to 22 July each year — around 63 days of continuous daylight. The exact dates shift slightly year to year. Outside this window, Tromsø still experiences very long days from late April through late August, with only brief twilight periods.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Is the midnight sun free to see?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Yes. The midnight sun is a natural phenomenon visible from anywhere outdoors in Tromsø. No ticket is required. Any website selling a "midnight sun ticket" or "midnight sun experience" is selling a tour, cable car ride, or boat trip — not access to the sun itself, which is always free.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Where is the best place to see the midnight sun in Tromsø?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Elevated viewpoints provide the clearest unobstructed view of the sun on the horizon at midnight. Fjellheisen cable car summit (421 m) is the most popular paid option. Telegrafbukta beach at the southern tip of Tromsøya is the best free ground-level viewpoint, with open westward views. Storsteinen mountain is reachable on foot for a free elevated view.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Does the midnight sun affect sleep in Tromsø?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Continuous daylight disrupts sleep patterns for many visitors. Most Tromsø hotels provide blackout curtains. A sleep mask is recommended for visitors sensitive to light. The effect varies by individual; some visitors adapt within a day or two.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Do I need a guide to see the midnight sun?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">No guide is needed. The midnight sun is visible from any outdoor location with a clear sky. Organised midnight sun tours are available through local operators but are optional. Check visittromso.no for weather forecasts and practical visiting information.</div>
    </div>
